HEADWORD: Haberdine
<hw>Hab`er*dine"</hw> <pr>(h⟦acr⟧b`⟦etil⟧r*d⟦emac⟧n" ⟦or⟧
h⟦acr⟧"b⟦etil⟧r*d⟦icr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[D.
<ets>abberdaan</ets>, <ets>labberdaan</ets>; or a French form, cf. OF.
<ets>habordeau</ets>, from the name of a Basque district, cf. F.
<ets>Labourd</ets>, adj. <ets>Labourdin.</ets> The <it>l</it> was
misunderstood as the French article.]</ety> <def>A cod salted and
dried.</def> <rj><au>Ainsworth.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

